&lt;p>Below you will find some information on how to run scripts.&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>You can find the most recent version of this guide &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/ahmadawais/create-guten-block" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>here&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;h2 id="--npm-start">👉 &lt;code>npm start&lt;/code>&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Use to compile and run the block in development mode.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Watches for any changes and reports back any errors in your code.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="--npm-run-build">👉 &lt;code>npm run build&lt;/code>&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Use to build production code for your block inside &lt;code>dist&lt;/code> folder.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Runs once and reports back the gzip file sizes of the produced code.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="--npm-run-eject">👉 &lt;code>npm run eject&lt;/code>&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Use to eject your plugin out of &lt;code>create-guten-block&lt;/code>.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Provides all the configurations so you can customize the project as you want.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>It&amp;rsquo;s a one-way street, &lt;code>eject&lt;/code> and you have to maintain everything yourself.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>You don&amp;rsquo;t normally have to &lt;code>eject&lt;/code> a project because by ejecting you lose the connection with &lt;code>create-guten-block&lt;/code> and from there onwards you have to update and maintain all the dependencies on your own.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
